<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-07-19T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-07-19T15:00:00-05:00" n="459" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d459">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">660M.116/9: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in Lithuania</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Kuykendall</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-07-19T16:00:00-04:00">July 19, 1935—4
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>8. Your despatch No. 266 of June 22, 1935.<note n="11" xml:id="d459fn11">Not printed.</note> Please request in writing
                                Lithuanian Foreign Office to furnish Legation with a statement
                                covering attitude of Lithuanian Government towards imports of
                                petroleum products from the United States and the policy that
                                Lithuania intends to pursue with respect to the issuance of import
                                licenses covering such products. Forward report by mail.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>